Very surprising, because in the
Granth Sahib all about the realized

00:34:54.056 --> 00:34:57.761
souls’ [Unclear: is written].
Here, sorrow is definitely there.

00:34:57.795 --> 00:35:02.744
There is no doubt about this;
depression must certainly happen here.

00:35:02.794 --> 00:35:10.378
That's why like fools they keep
reading them, do nothing. [Unclear]

00:35:10.424 --> 00:35:13.570
Even in Gurudwaras, in
the Granth Sahib, there’s

00:35:13.594 --> 00:35:16.740
nothing that isn’t specially
found in Nanak Sahib.

00:35:16.774 --> 00:35:21.740
But he included all the realized
souls—what Kabir, all, whoever he found.

00:35:21.741 --> 00:35:25.777
Be it Kabir or Nagdev,
whoever they were—he compiled

00:35:25.801 --> 00:35:29.440
the Granth Sahib with
all the realized souls.

00:35:29.506 --> 00:35:35.357
But those who read it must themselves be
depressive—what can be done about that?

00:35:35.391 --> 00:35:42.857
All those whose minds
are messed up—God save!

00:35:42.882 --> 00:35:45.773
Because… [Unclear]

00:35:45.798 --> 00:35:49.220
And secondly, it's a place
where they don’t know

00:35:49.244 --> 00:35:53.032
about realized souls,
nothing—they read like fools.

00:35:53.118 --> 00:35:56.964
Nanak Sahib said everything—he
said, search what is inside;

00:35:56.988 --> 00:36:00.634
search! They're just reading
“search, search, search.”

